references.paper_title: High-resolution image synthesis with latent diffusion models
references.reason: This work is fundamental to the development of high-resolution image synthesis using latent diffusion models, a key technology used by the current paper.
This paper introduces denoising diffusion probabilistic models (DDPMs), the foundation for diffusion models explored in the current paper.

references.paper_title: Progressive distillation for fast sampling of diffusion models
references.reason: This paper introduces progressive distillation and serves as a foundational paper for the distillation of diffusion models, which is the focus of this paper.

references.paper_title: Concept sliders: Lora adaptors for precise control in diffusion models
references.reason: This paper introduces Concept Sliders, a control mechanism used to seamlessly transfer to distilled models, demonstrating that distilled models preserve the concept representations of base models
This work discusses multi-concept customization of text-to-image diffusion models, which is used in this paper.
